President Obama issued a statement expressing condolences for the loss of life and devastation caused by recent storms in the Philippines, particularly Tropical Storm Ketsana. The United States has been assisting the people of the Philippines through military forces and civilian agencies by distributing relief supplies and helping in rescuing victims. The U.S. Agency for International Development has allocated $1.8 million to respond to the disaster. The statement emphasizes the long history of friendship and cooperation between the United States and the Philippines and the commitment to continue providing assistance in the coming days.